window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>Psychology of...Horror Villains, Survivors, and Victims: Movie Edition, Volume II </i>expands on the first volume with more character analysis. In volume one, S.L. Yarbrough used her degree to analyze iconic characters such as Michael Myers, Jason, Pinhead, Dr. Frankenstein, and many more.</p> <p>In volume two, not only are there more characters such as Samara from <i>The Ring</i>, Vlad Tepes III (Dracula), the Thir13en Ghosts, Blade, and Jack Torrance, but also true-crime stories, strange facts, and interviews with horror film director Jesse Kozel and professional ghost hunter Bea Brugge.</p> <p><i>Psychology of...Horror Villains, Survivors, and Victims</i> can be used as a reference guide to psychological disorders, horror movies, and horror villains. The series is perfect for psychology majors, criminal justice majors, true-crime fans, and anyone who loves horror films and psychology.</p>"; 
